        "If a question mentions password, fingerprint, smart card, or biometric -> it's authentication. If it mentions permissions, ACL, or 'allowed to' -> it's authorization.",
        "Encryption protects data confidentiality even if storage/transmission is compromised — it is NOT the same as access control.",
